"{\"abstract\":\"This paper proposes a new vectorial total variation prior (VTV) for color images. Different from existing VTVs, our VTV, named the decorrelated vectorial total variation prior (D-VTV), measures the discrete gradients of the luminance component and that of the chrominance one in a separated manner, which significantly reduces undesirable uneven color effects. Moreover, a higher-order generalization of the D-VTV, which we call the decorrelated vectorial total generalized variation prior (D-VTGV), is also developed for avoiding the staircasing effect that accompanies the use of VTVs. A noteworthy property of the D-VT(G)V is that it enables us to efficiently minimize objective functions involving it by a primal-dual splitting method. Experimental results illustrate their utility.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2193320\",\"name\":\"S. Ono\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2193320\"},{\"authorId\":\"145889563\",\"name\":\"I. Yamada\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/145889563\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"145595269\",\"name\":\"Satoshi Sato\"},{\"authorId\":\"35158117\",\"name\":\"Nobuhiko Wakai\"},{\"authorId\":\"34785090\",\"name\":\"Kunio Nobori\"},{\"authorId\":\"2540511\",\"name\":\"T. Azuma\"},{\"authorId\":\"2515755\",\"name\":\"T. Miyata\"},{\"authorId\":\"2708286\",\"name\":\"M. Nakashizuka\"}],\"doi\":\"10.23919/MVA.2017.7986768\",\"intent\":[\"background\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"ea670f0763f9e09c1f128f2ab6045433830d7b76\",\"title\":\"Compressive color sensing using random complementary color filter array\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/ea670f0763f9e09c1f128f2ab6045433830d7b76\",\"venue\":\"2017 Fifteenth IAPR International Conference on Machine Vision Applications (MVA)\",\"year\":2017},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"18159121\",\"name\":\"Saori Takeyama\"},{\"authorId\":\"2193320\",\"name\